        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 22 at 6:00AM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 600 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Tupman, or 24 miles west of Bakersfield, moving
north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wasco, Tupman, Buttonwillow, Harris Ranch, and Lost Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
